{
  "stem": "10359.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Mark Grinims.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm from the town called Ostrog, Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My name of father is Zev.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother's name was Eska.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had one brother and one sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister was murdered in 1942 in the town Rovno.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my brother died in the United States of natural causes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister's name was Sonia, and my brother's name was Henry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I-- Ostrog in gen-- in general was a very beautiful city, full of meadows, full of lilac trees and apple trees, a lot of grass and rivers.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was an idyllic place with no pollution, no noise.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the people used to come from all over for vacation to Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used to live in a fairly comfortable house, but a big house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's about all I can remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My childhood is uneventful per se because I lived very comfortable.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I attended private public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I attend private high school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had friends from different religion, Jewish and non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I got along very well within the community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I also belonged to the Betar organization, which was a Zionist organization, when I was a teenager up till the age of-- up to the year 1939 until the Soviets came into our town, where all the temples and all the organizations were disband, especially the Jewish ones.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that's about all I can remember of my childhood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My, my sister lived at home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She went to private high school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My brother was studying abroad in Austria, medicine, and then in Sorbonne in Paris.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To a point, yes-- not orthodox religious, but religious to a point.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I want a temple only on, on major holidays.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And but I was aware because being part of the Zionist organization, which was very nationalistic, I was involved with all of this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a pharmacist and until he died in 1935--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--of natural causes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother died when I was fairly young.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father remarried about 10 years after my mother died.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had a very good stepmother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was very comfortable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fanny.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she came from the south border of Poland, Austria.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she spoke fluently German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that later on would, would have had an influence on me to remain in Ostrog because she didn't believe that the Germans will do what they did.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's why I remained for a while.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was killed in the second, the massacre in Ostrog in 1941.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In '22, actually.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it's only one day difference.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Somehow it mixed up in one day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the, the Ostrog-- the Jewish history of Ostrog is very interesting.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It became in the 1400s, circa 1400s in 40, 40, [? 50. ?] And it was quite a few Jews immigrated from Germany, from England.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were quite well-off until they were told to leave about 40, 50 years later because there were some conflicts between the Polish king and Lithuanian king.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were-- and then they came back 50 years later.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were dealing with exporting wheat and tem-- timber and wax and all that to Poland, to, to other countries.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then in the 1600s or so, we had the massacre of about 7,000 Jews through a Ukrainian Cossack man named Khmelnytsky.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And after the massacre of 7,000 people, about five families remained.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it took quite a few years-- about 50 or so years-- to establish a new community, Jewish community, in Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After that, we still had some little, what you call pogroms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the Tatars, which were lived in our area, helped the Jews at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then in the 16-- in the 1700s and 1800s, Ostrog had about 10,000 or more Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the, the Jewish community prospered very well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was the center of the Hasidic community and all the schools and all of Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the more prominent rabbis from all of Poland were-- came to lecture and to teach at the yeshivas in Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Then we also had a lot of Zionist organizations, about six or seven of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Everybody had different uniforms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They felt very free.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And this was the golden age-- so to say, up to '39-- of the Jews in Ostrog because they paraded in their uniforms.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They felt very free to express their nationalistic feelings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So everything was fine until the Soviets came in and disband all of this, and then the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And after the Soviets came, naturally, everything changed because you couldn't have any businesses, even though my stepmother was still had the-- she was still alive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she still continued to work in that drugstore that my father had.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But then gradually, they closed all those stores because they considered them being capitalistic.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
